1
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:08,550
(digital tone)

2
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:16,391
{\an8}(peaceful music in
foreign language)

3
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:43,937
(chimes)

4
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:46,564
- [Narrator] Shkrei, having
passed the national exams,

5
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:49,317
is on her way to attend
the initiation ceremony

6
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,986
for those eligible to
become court officials.

7
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:54,322
It's the beginning
step for Saiunkoku's

8
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:56,783
first ever female official.

9
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:58,827
- It certainly is
a fine day today.

10
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:00,286
- [Shkrei] You're right!

11
00:02:00,328 --> 00:02:01,746
Well, Father, Seiran,
I'll be on my way now.

12
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,499
- All right, be sure
to do your best.

13
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:05,875
- Okay.

14
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:09,713
(traditional Japanese music)

15
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:18,972
- [Shkei] Are you prepared for
the ceremony, Your Majesty?

16
00:02:19,014 --> 00:02:21,725
- Yes, has everyone
been assembled?

17
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:23,852
- Yes, mostly.

18
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:26,688
Though I'm afraid there is one
person who hasn't shown up.

19
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:28,398
(laughs)

20
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:32,569
(traditional Japanese music)

21
00:02:32,610 --> 00:02:34,529
- What a beautiful day.

22
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:35,447
- Quite.

23
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:40,577
- [Reishin] Ah, what a
lovely day it is, KMyk.

24
00:02:40,618 --> 00:02:43,455
The sky has the exact
same color as that day.

25
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:47,042
The day you passed the exam in
first place at the age of 16.

26
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,793
You spent the rest
of the day running

27
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:50,712
from high-ranking
officials wanting you

28
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:52,255
to become their son-in-law.

29
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:54,257
Hm.

30
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:57,844
What're you looking at, KMyk?

31
00:02:57,886 --> 00:02:59,387
- [KMyk] I was just
wondering, sir,

32
00:02:59,429 --> 00:03:01,556
about you acting as
Shkrei's sponsor.

33
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:03,558
Are you still intending to
keep that a secret from her?

34
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:07,979
- Hm, I have to tell her
that I'm her uncle first.

35
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:10,357
- In other words, not
for quite a while.

36
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:13,401
- The best things in life should
always be saved for later.

37
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:15,612
- Hm.

38
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,491
- [Announcer] Lord Reishin
Hong, Senior Secretary

39
00:03:19,532 --> 00:03:20,700
of the Department
of Civil Affairs,

40
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:23,453
and Lord KMyk Li,
Assistant Secretary

41
00:03:23,495 --> 00:03:26,414
of the Department of Civil
Affairs have arrived.

42
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:28,750
(footsteps)

43
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:30,835
- [Kijin] There's
more of a commotion

44
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,504
today than there
was when KMyk Li

45
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:34,381
and Shkei Ran passed the exams.

46
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:35,840
- That was only to be expected.

47
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:38,551
After all, look at who the
top three ended up being.

48
00:03:40,804 --> 00:03:42,472
- [Official] Eigetsu Tou.

49
00:03:42,514 --> 00:03:45,684
He passed the exams and took
first place at the age of 13.

50
00:03:45,725 --> 00:03:48,061
It smashed Lord KMyk's
record with ease.

51
00:03:48,103 --> 00:03:49,771
- [Official] Second
place went to Rykren Ran,

52
00:03:49,813 --> 00:03:51,940
the younger brother of
General Ran, isn't that right?

53
00:03:51,981 --> 00:03:53,775
- [Official] Yes, but
skipping the initiation

54
00:03:53,817 --> 00:03:55,443
ceremony is unheard of.

55
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:56,945
- [Official] This
is an odd year.

56
00:03:56,986 --> 00:03:58,905
As soon as the national
civil service examination

57
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:02,784
system was open to women, one
came in and took third place.

58
00:04:02,826 --> 00:04:04,327
- [Official] You
know, that girl looks

59
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:06,329
an awful lot like the princess
who entered the royal harem.

60
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:07,706
- [Official] Yes, now
that you mention it.

61
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:08,873
- Really?

62
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:10,625
I thought she looked
more like that young boy

63
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,711
who was working for
the department of
finance last summer.

64
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,671
Perhaps they're
siblings or relatives.

65
00:04:14,713 --> 00:04:16,548
- Sounds like things will
get hectic around here.

66
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:18,383
- [Kijin] I'm sure
she's prepared for it.

67
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:20,343
She has to handle
things on her own.

68
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:21,803
All we can do is
wait for her to claw

69
00:04:21,845 --> 00:04:23,638
her way up to where we sit.

70
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,432
Don't you agree, Reishin?

71
00:04:25,473 --> 00:04:27,892
- Yes, you're quite
right about that.

72
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:29,811
- [Announcer] The
king of Saiunkoku,

73
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:32,897
His Majesty Rykki
Shi, has arrived.

74
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:37,986
- Things are finally
getting underway.

75
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:40,905
- Why don't we sit back and
observe these youngsters

76
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,366
as they work together
to create a new era?

77
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:46,077
- [Announcer] When we
call your name, stand up.

78
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:49,164
This year, passing in first
place, Jougen Eigetsu Tou.

79
00:04:49,205 --> 00:04:50,040
- Yes.

80
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:54,753
- And second place,
Bougen Rykren Ran.

81
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:00,508
(clears throat)

82
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:03,595
Third place Tanka Shkrei Hong.

83
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:04,637
- Yes.

84
00:05:04,679 --> 00:05:07,390
(crowd murmurs)

85
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:14,606
- The aforementioned top
three are hereby acknowledged

86
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:16,775
for their outstanding
achievements.

87
00:05:17,776 --> 00:05:18,651
- Hm.

88
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:26,910
(exclaims)

89
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:29,204
- [Shkrei] Miss KochM!

90
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:30,789
- Huh?

91
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:33,541
- Big news, today was the
initiation ceremony and huh?

92
00:05:34,918 --> 00:05:37,045
- I'm sorry to have to
tell you this, Shkrei,

93
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:40,173
but it would be best if you
stopped coming here for a while.

94
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:41,091
(exclaims)

95
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:43,593
(sad music)

96
00:05:47,222 --> 00:05:50,809
- Oh, right, I almost
forgot, we're out of salt.

97
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:52,894
Maybe I have a bag
of salt please?

98
00:05:52,936 --> 00:05:54,104
- Sure thing.

99
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:55,021
Oh...

100
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:56,940
- Huh?

101
00:05:59,776 --> 00:06:01,820
It must be getting late,
I'd better hurry on home.

102
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:04,781
Lord KMyk and General Ran
will be arriving soon.

103
00:06:04,823 --> 00:06:06,199
Huh, ah!

104
00:06:06,241 --> 00:06:08,743
Hello there, ma'am, is your
back feeling any better?

105
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:10,870
- Ah, yes, yes, thank you.

106
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:12,038
(fast footsteps)

107
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:12,914
- Huh?

108
00:06:12,956 --> 00:06:14,207
(gasps)

109
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:15,125
Ah, hm.

110
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:21,840
- Excuse me, My Lord.

111
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:23,049
- [Angry Lord] This is absurd!

112
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:24,759
You're saying you lost the ring?

113
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:27,512
The ring signifies
leadership of the Sa clan!

114
00:06:27,554 --> 00:06:28,722
We only just found it.

115
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,849
How could you let this
happen, you idiots?

116
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:33,268
I already reported
that it had been found.

117
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:35,061
If they realize I don't have it,

118
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:38,273
that reward money and chance
for promotion will be lost.

119
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:40,942
KochM, I'm sorry, but I won't
be staying here tonight.

120
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:43,236
- What a shame,
that's really too bad.

121
00:06:43,278 --> 00:06:46,614
(bird calls)

122
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:47,490
(clatters)

123
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:48,158
- Hm?

124
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,160
(groans)

125
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:52,787
Let me guess, you got lost
on your way here again?

126
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:53,955
- Just shut up.

127
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:55,665
Besides, that's not important.

128
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:57,167
I'm more interested
in the recent rumors

129
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,502
about you going to
that brothel again.

130
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:01,171
- You shouldn't be
so jealous, KMyk.

131
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,715
I'm just a normal, healthy,
adult male after all.

132
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:04,841
- Forget the brothel!

133
00:07:04,883 --> 00:07:05,925
What you need is
a doctor who will

134
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,510
fix that stupid head of yours.

135
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:10,263
- C'mon, at least I'm
doing my work sufficiently.

136
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:12,182
For example, I
received a report that

137
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:13,600
that ring has been found.

138
00:07:13,641 --> 00:07:15,101
- What, really?

139
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,270
- Yes, but apparently it got
lost again soon afterwards.

140
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:18,688
- What's that supposed to mean?

141
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,148
Is this some kind of joke?

142
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,608
(chuckles)

143
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:23,068
- Forget it, why
don't we head on over

144
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:25,737
to Shkrei's house and enjoy
some of her home cooking?

145
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:27,739
Today's a day to celebrate.

146
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:31,576
(contemplative music)

147
00:07:31,618 --> 00:07:32,869
- [Shkrei] I don't
get it, it's not like

148
00:07:32,911 --> 00:07:34,788
I've changed at all.

149
00:07:34,829 --> 00:07:37,040
(grunts)

150
00:07:37,082 --> 00:07:38,333
- Ah, I'm so sorry.

151
00:07:38,375 --> 00:07:41,211
- Eigetsu? (gasps)

152
00:07:41,252 --> 00:07:43,755
Don't tell me you got
into another fight.

153
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:44,673
- I don't know.

154
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:46,716
It sure does look that way.

155
00:07:46,758 --> 00:07:48,259
- (sighs) What a relief.

156
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:51,846
At least I didn't run into
your other personality.

157
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:53,181
- [Seiran] Lady Shkrei!

158
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:54,933
I've been looking
all over for you.

159
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:55,850
- Hello Seiran.

160
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:57,310
- Mr. Seiran.

161
00:07:57,352 --> 00:07:59,896
- Oh, I didn't realize you
were with Eigetsu, My Lady.

162
00:07:59,938 --> 00:08:01,106
- [Eigetsu] Yes.

163
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,899
- Still, I thought I
made it clear to you

164
00:08:02,941 --> 00:08:04,317
that you shouldn't be
going out on your own.

165
00:08:04,359 --> 00:08:06,653
It's too risky and dangerous.

166
00:08:06,695 --> 00:08:08,697
The initiates have just
received their salaries,

167
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,615
meaning each of you has
a large sum of money.

168
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:12,701
That makes you prime
targets for thugs.

169
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:14,703
Hm, Eigetsu, you're all beat up.

170
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:16,788
Don't tell me you've already
been attacked by them.

171
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:18,289
- No, I haven't and
they couldn't have

172
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:19,916
gotten anything if they tried.

173
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:22,961
I sent all the 80 silver
coins back to my hometown.

174
00:08:23,003 --> 00:08:25,088
- [Seiran] You sent all of it?

175
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:26,297
- Uh-huh.

176
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,341
- Then why did you end
up getting into a fight?

177
00:08:28,383 --> 00:08:29,884
- Well, from what
I can remember,

178
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:32,220
I was in the estate of
some kind of nobleman.

179
00:08:32,262 --> 00:08:34,681
He was forcing me to
drink wine with him.

180
00:08:34,723 --> 00:08:36,891
And he kept asking me if I'd
like to marry his daughter.

181
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:39,269
- [Shkrei] You got into a
fight at a nobleman's house?

182
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:41,021
- No, I made a run
for it right after

183
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,689
he forced me to drink the wine

184
00:08:42,731 --> 00:08:45,150
so I doubt I fought
anyone or made a scene.

185
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,152
- I think it'd probably
be in your best interests

186
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:50,071
to turn down all banquet
invitations from now on.

187
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:53,742
- You did pass the exam with
the title of Jougen after all.

188
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:56,619
Those who place in the top
tier enjoy many privileges

189
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:58,413
so naturally many people
who would like to become

190
00:08:58,455 --> 00:09:00,331
a relative or an
in-law to a promising

191
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:02,667
future official will
approach you like that.

192
00:09:02,709 --> 00:09:03,668
- Good point.

193
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:04,794
It makes a lot more sense when

194
00:09:04,836 --> 00:09:06,087
you put it like
that, Mr. Seiran.

195
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:07,797
- You did write a
letter to the people

196
00:09:07,839 --> 00:09:10,383
in your hometown to tell them
you passed the exam, right?

197
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:11,926
- No.

198
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,261
The Department of
Protocols said they would

199
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:15,138
send a messenger by
horse to notify everybody

200
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:17,432
so I just gave the money to
the messenger to deliver.

201
00:09:17,474 --> 00:09:19,768
- (groans) Later I'll
give you some paper

202
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:22,062
and I want you to write a
letter by the end of the day.

203
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:23,188
- Huh, but why?

204
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,397
- No buts!

205
00:09:24,439 --> 00:09:25,648
You have to tell
everyone back home

206
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:26,816
that you passed the exam.

207
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:28,109
It's really important.

208
00:09:28,151 --> 00:09:30,070
Think about all the
people who are waiting

209
00:09:30,111 --> 00:09:31,780
for word about your results.

210
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:34,324
They'll be much happier to
hear it from you directly.

211
00:09:36,034 --> 00:09:37,285
- Thanks a lot Shkrei.

212
00:09:37,327 --> 00:09:38,703
- [Shkrei] Besides,
you should write

213
00:09:38,745 --> 00:09:41,289
in order to ensure the
safety of your money as well.

214
00:09:41,331 --> 00:09:42,165
- What?

215
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:43,667
Ensure its safety?

216
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:44,709
It's not safe?

217
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:45,919
- Of course it's not safe.

218
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,754
Sending all 80
silver coins at once?

219
00:09:47,796 --> 00:09:49,130
That's way too much.

220
00:09:49,172 --> 00:09:50,799
Even if you go through the
Department of Protocol,

221
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,092
in the hands of the
wrong messenger,

222
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:54,010
it's only possible
that half of that money

223
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:55,679
will make it to its destination.

224
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,389
The money should've been
sent in lots of separate,

225
00:09:57,430 --> 00:10:00,433
small amounts that
wouldn't be worth stealing.

226
00:10:00,475 --> 00:10:01,393
- Really?

227
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:02,977
Wow, you're amazing, Shkrei.

228
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:05,021
You sure know how to
deal with money issues.

229
00:10:05,063 --> 00:10:05,897
(gasps)

230
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:07,065
- [Seiran] It's true.

231
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:08,191
When it comes to money,
I don't think anyone

232
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:10,026
is as clever as Lady Shkrei.

233
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:11,736
- Hey, stop it, you two.

234
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:13,863
(laughs)

235
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:17,992
- [Father] By the
way, when will Shkrei

236
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:19,911
and the others in her
group receive notice

237
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:21,871
of their placements, Lord KMyk?

238
00:10:21,913 --> 00:10:23,415
- From what I've heard,
I believe you should

239
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:26,251
be receiving some sort of
written notice about that soon.

240
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:28,378
- Oh, yes, of course, I see.

241
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:31,756
- So this year's national
exam was rather controversial.

242
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:33,174
- For starters, how about
your younger brother

243
00:10:33,216 --> 00:10:35,385
skipping the
initiation ceremony?

244
00:10:35,427 --> 00:10:37,220
- I have to admit
that one is beyond

245
00:10:37,262 --> 00:10:39,180
even the limits of
my comprehension.

246
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:41,057
True, I did expect
him to run away

247
00:10:41,099 --> 00:10:43,476
but I didn't expect it
would happen so quickly.

248
00:10:43,518 --> 00:10:46,021
- A case of like older
brother, like younger brother.

249
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:48,940
Good lord, neither one of you
can take anything seriously.

250
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:51,401
- I have to say that he's quite

251
00:10:51,443 --> 00:10:55,113
an amazing person in many
