kick his brains out.

267
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:27,020
I only restrained
myself because he's

268
00:11:27,062 --> 00:11:29,356
General Ran's younger brother.

269
00:11:29,397 --> 00:11:31,900
- It's very generous of
you to restrain yourself.

270
00:11:31,941 --> 00:11:35,236
- (gasps) Sorry, I didn't
mean to talk like that.

271
00:11:35,278 --> 00:11:36,488
- Don't worry about it, Shkrei.

272
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:39,074
After all, you were
only telling the truth.

273
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:40,950
- So I bet you two
are looking forward

274
00:11:40,992 --> 00:11:42,494
to your new job tomorrow.

275
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:43,453
- Yes.

276
00:11:43,495 --> 00:11:45,830
Let's both do our best, Eigetsu.

277
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:47,082
- Yep, you bet.

278
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:53,421
I'm looking forward

279
00:11:53,463 --> 00:11:55,215
to finding out where
we'll be assigned.

280
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:57,425
- Me too, I wonder where
the two of us will end up.

281
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:59,302
Although to be
completely honest,

282
00:11:59,344 --> 00:12:00,804
I really hope I'm not assigned

283
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:02,931
anywhere near the
central palace.

284
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:07,852
What should I do?

285
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:10,105
